Business Brief -- Noranda Inc.:
   Sale of Nine Million Shares
   Of Hemlo Gold Is Slated
Noranda said it expects net proceeds from the sale to be
C$95 million, which will be used to help pay down the
company's C$4.5 billion debt.
   Following the sale, Noranda's stake in Hemlo will drop to
45.7% from 55% currently. Last June, Toronto-based Hemlo
acquired all of Noranda's gold assets in exchange for 8.6
million Hemlo common shares. There are about 96 million Hemlo
shares currently outstanding. Noranda, also based in Toronto,
has interests in forest products and oil and gas.